```text
You are working in a React Native (Expo) TypeScript repo.

SOURCE OF TRUTH:
- Always read MASTER_PLAN.md and TODO.md before coding.
- Implement ONLY what is in TODO.md for the current sprint.
- If there is conflict, MASTER_PLAN.md wins.
- If a task is ambiguous, choose the simplest implementation consistent with the plan.

ARCHITECTURE RULES:
- AI never mutates state. AI outputs proposals only.
- Only Applier/Repository writes to SQLite.
- Domain logic must be pure functions and unit-tested.
- UI components must not contain business rules (keep logic in domain/).

TEST-FIRST:
- For domain logic, write Jest unit tests first.
- Keep tests deterministic; mock AI.
- Prefer small, focused tests.

CODE STYLE:
- TypeScript strict, no any (unless justified with comment).
- Favor small modules with clear interfaces.
- Add minimal documentation comments to public interfaces.

DELIVERABLES:
- When adding a feature, include:
  - types/schemas
  - tests
  - minimal UI wiring
  - repository changes (with migration if needed)
```
